> Of all the delicious meats we get from our British butchers - Roaming Roosters - these spiced fennel sausages are by far André's favourite. Even though we all love a bit of potato with our sausages, we thought as it's spring, it's out with the old and in with the new. So, enjoy the sausages with this herby couscous and North African chermoula sauce.

Pre-heat your #grill{} to medium-high. Pour the @couscous{3/4%cup} into a #heatproof bowl{} and season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. Stir in @oil{1%tbsp} and then pour in @boiling water{300%ml}. Cover your bowl with a #plate{} or #clingfilm{} and leave for ~{10%minutes}.

Cut the @red onion{1} in half through the root, peel and then chop into 1/2cm pieces (or as small as you can). Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}. Remove the core from the @orange pepper{1} and thinly slice.

Heat a #saucepan{} over medium heat, add @oil{1%tbsp} and add the chopped onion. Cook for ~{3%minutes}, then add the sliced orange pepper and cook for another ~{3%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and the @chermoula spice mix{2%tbsp} and cook for ~{1%minute} longer. Pour in the @tomato passata{1%cup} and cook over a medium heat for ~{12%minutes}.

While your sauce cooks, pop the @Tuscan pork sausage{4} under your grill and cook for ~{8-10%minutes} on each side. They are cooked when the centre is no longer pink.

Keep one eye on your sausages and get chopping the @mint{5%sprigs} and @flat leaf parsley{5%sprigs}. Zest the @lemon{1} and stir the herbs and zest into your couscous. Squeeze in the juice of half the lemon and check the seasoning. Add more salt and pepper if you feel it needs it!

Serve your sausages on a bed of couscous and finish with your chermoula spiced tomato sauce and a dollop of cooling @Greek style natural yoghurt{1}.